From 1111111111111111111111111111111111111111 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 15:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: broadcom: bcm2712-rpi-5-b: add ramoops reserved
 memory

Add a 1 MiB reserved-memory region and wire a ramoops backend so panic/oops
state is persisted across reboot for lab post-mortem workflows.

This patch is gated by IOTGW_ENABLE_CRASH_DEBUG_DEV in the Yocto recipe and is
not enabled for baseline production builds.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [lab-only crash-debug profile]
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts
index ad96fb439bd2..0466e7275fd3 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dts
@@ -105,6 +105,24 @@ / {
 			};
 		};
 	};
+
+	reserved-memory {
+		#address-cells = <2>;
+		#size-cells = <2>;
+		ranges;
+
+		ramoops_region: ramoops@13000000 {
+			reg = <0x0 0x13000000 0x0 0x00100000>;
+		};
+	};
+
+	ramoops {
+		compatible = "ramoops";
+		memory-region = <&ramoops_region>;
+		record-size = <0x00020000>;
+		console-size = <0x00020000>;
+		pmsg-size = <0x00020000>;
+	};
 };
 
 &rp1_spi0 {
-- 
